{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.6",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 6 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:1",
      "text": "My son, if you have become collateral for your neighbor, if you have struck your hands in pledge for a stranger,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:2",
      "text": "you are trapped by the words of your mouth; you are ensnared with the words of your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:3",
      "text": "Do this now, my son, and deliver yourself, since you have come into the hand of your neighbor. Go, humble yourself. Press your plea with your neighbor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:4",
      "text": "Give no sleep to your eyes, nor slumber to your eyelids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:5",
      "text": "Free yourself, like a gazelle from the hand of the hunter, like a bird from the snare of the fowler.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:6",
      "text": "Go to the ant, you sluggard. Consider her ways, and be wise;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:7",
      "text": "which having no chief, overseer, or ruler,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:8",
      "text": "provides her bread in the summer, and gathers her food in the harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:9",
      "text": "How long will you sleep, sluggard? When will you arise out of your sleep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:10",
      "text": "A little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep —",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:11",
      "text": "so your poverty will come as a robber, and your scarcity as an armed man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:12",
      "text": "A worthless person, a man of iniquity, is he who walks with a perverse mouth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:13",
      "text": "who winks with his eyes, who signals with his feet, who motions with his fingers,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:14",
      "text": "in whose heart is perverseness, who devises evil continually, who always sows discord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:15",
      "text": "Therefore his calamity will come suddenly. He will be broken suddenly, and that without remedy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:16",
      "text": "There are six things which Yahweh hates; yes, seven which are an abomination to him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:17",
      "text": "arrogant eyes, a lying tongue, hands that shed innocent blood,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:18",
      "text": "a heart that devises wicked schemes, feet that are swift in running to mischief,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:19",
      "text": "a false witness who utters lies, and he who sows discord among brothers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:20",
      "text": "My son, keep your father ’s commandment, and don’t forsake your mother’s teaching.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:21",
      "text": "Bind them continually on your heart. Tie them around your neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:22",
      "text": "When you walk, it will lead you. When you sleep, it will watch over you. When you awake, it will talk with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:23",
      "text": "For the commandment is a lamp, and the law is light. Reproofs of instruction are the way of life,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:24",
      "text": "to keep you from the immoral woman, from the flattery of the wayward wife’s tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:25",
      "text": "Don’t lust after her beauty in your heart, neither let her captivate you with her eyelids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:26",
      "text": "For a prostitute reduces you to a piece of bread. The adulteress hunts for your precious life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:27",
      "text": "Can a man scoop fire into his lap, and his clothes not be burned?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:28",
      "text": "Or can one walk on hot coals, and his feet not be scorched?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:29",
      "text": "So is he who goes in to his neighbor ’s wife. Whoever touches her will not be unpunished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:30",
      "text": "Men don’t despise a thief if he steals to satisfy himself when he is hungry,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:31",
      "text": "but if he is found, he shall restore seven times. He shall give all the wealth of his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:32",
      "text": "He who commits adultery with a woman is void of understanding. He who does it destroys his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:33",
      "text": "He will get wounds and dishonor. His reproach will not be wiped away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:34",
      "text": "For jealousy arouses the fury of the husband. He won’t spare in the day of vengeance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.6.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:35",
      "text": "He won’t regard any ransom, neither will he rest content, though you give many gifts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
